# Coding Standards

## File Size Limit

**CRITICAL: Maximum 500 lines per file**

When a file approaches or exceeds 500 lines:
1. Extract reusable logic into utility functions
2. Split large components into smaller sub-components
3. Move business logic to services or hooks
4. Use the directory structure to organize related files

### Example Refactoring

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - 800 lines in one file
// features/borrow/components/borrow-form.tsx (800 lines)

// ✅ GOOD - Split into smaller files
// features/borrow/components/borrow-form/
//   ├── index.tsx (50 lines)
//   ├── borrow-form.tsx (200 lines)
//   ├── collateral-section.tsx (150 lines)
//   ├── borrow-section.tsx (150 lines)
//   ├── summary-section.tsx (100 lines)
//   ├── validation.ts (80 lines)
//   └── types.ts (50 lines)
```

## Code Organization

### Import Order

```typescript
// 1. React and Next.js
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { useRouter } from 'next/navigation';
import Image from 'next/image';

// 2. External libraries
import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import clsx from 'clsx';

// 3. Internal features
import { BorrowService } from '@/features/borrow/services';
import { useBorrowForm } from '@/features/borrow/hooks';

// 4. Shared components and hooks
import { Button, Card } from '@/shared/components';
import { useWallet } from '@/shared/hooks';

// 5. Config and constants
import { APP_CONFIG } from '@/config';
import { ROUTES } from '@/shared/constants';

// 6. Utils and helpers
import { cn } from '@/shared/utils/cn';
import { formatCurrency } from '@/shared/utils/format';

// 7. Types
import type { BorrowFormData } from './types';
import type { Token } from '@/shared/types';

// 8. Styles
import './styles.css';
```

### Function Order in Components

```typescript
export const Component: React.FC<Props> = (props) => {
  // 1. Hooks (useState, useEffect, custom hooks)
  const [state, setState] = useState();
  const router = useRouter();
  const { data } = useCustomHook();
  
  // 2. Derived state and memoized values
  const derivedValue = useMemo(() => compute(state), [state]);
  
  // 3. Event handlers
  const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
    // Handler logic
  }, []);
  
  const handleSubmit = useCallback(async (e: FormEvent) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    // Submit logic
  }, []);
  
  // 4. Effects
  useEffect(() => {
    // Effect logic
  }, []);
  
  // 5. Early returns
  if (isLoading) return <LoadingSpinner />;
  if (error) return <ErrorMessage error={error} />;
  if (!data) return null;
  
  // 6. Render helpers
  const renderContent = () => {
    return <div>{/* Complex rendering */}</div>;
  };
  
  // 7. Main return
  return (
    <div>
      {renderContent()}
    </div>
  );
};
```

## Naming Conventions

### Files and Folders

```
// Components (kebab-case)
hero-section/
  ├── index.tsx
  ├── hero-section.tsx
  └── hero-section.types.ts

// Hooks (kebab-case with use- prefix)
use-borrow-form.ts
use-wallet-connection.ts

// Services (kebab-case with .service suffix)
borrow-api.service.ts
user-api.service.ts

// Utils (kebab-case)
format-currency.ts
validate-email.ts

// Types (kebab-case)
borrow-types.ts
user-types.ts

// Constants (SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE for file if all constants)
constants.ts (or ROUTES.ts if specific)
```

### Variables and Functions

```typescript
// Variables - camelCase
const userName = 'John';
const isLoading = false;
const userAge = 25;

// Functions - camelCase, verb prefix
const getUserData = () => {};
const handleSubmit = () => {};
const calculateTotal = () => {};
const validateForm = () => {};

// Boolean variables - is/has/should prefix
const isValid = true;
const hasError = false;
const shouldRender = true;
const canSubmit = false;

// Constants - SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE
const MAX_RETRY_COUNT = 3;
const API_BASE_URL = 'https://api.example.com';
const DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 5000;

// React Components - PascalCase
const UserProfile = () => {};
const BorrowForm = () => {};
const MetricCard = () => {};

// Types and Interfaces - PascalCase
interface User {}
type UserRole = string;
interface ButtonProps {}
```

## Error Handling

### Try-Catch Pattern

```typescript
const fetchUserData = async (userId: string) => {
  try {
    const response = await fetch(`/api/users/${userId}`);
    
    if (!response.ok) {
      throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}: ${response.statusText}`);
    }
    
    const data = await response.json();
    return { data, error: null };
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Failed to fetch user data:', error);
    return {
      data: null,
      error: error instanceof Error ? error.message : 'Unknown error',
    };
  }
};
```

### React Query Error Handling

```typescript
const { data, isError, error } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['user', userId],
  queryFn: () => fetchUser(userId),
  retry: (failureCount, error) => {
    // Don't retry on 404
    if (error.message.includes('404')) return false;
    return failureCount < 3;
  },
});

if (isError) {
  return <ErrorMessage message={error.message} />;
}
```

## Performance Best Practices

### 1. Memoization

```typescript
// ✅ Memoize expensive calculations
const expensiveValue = useMemo(() => {
  return items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.price, 0);
}, [items]);

// ✅ Memoize callbacks
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  console.log('Clicked');
}, []);

// ✅ Memoize components
const MemoizedComponent = memo(ExpensiveComponent);
```

### 2. Lazy Loading

```typescript
// Lazy load routes
const BorrowPage = lazy(() => import('@/features/borrow/borrow-page'));

// Lazy load heavy components
const Chart = lazy(() => import('./chart'));

// Usage with Suspense
<Suspense fallback={<LoadingSpinner />}>
  <Chart data={data} />
</Suspense>
```

### 3. Avoid Inline Object/Array Creation

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Creates new object on every render
<Component style={{ margin: 10 }} />

// ✅ GOOD - Define outside or memoize
const style = { margin: 10 };
<Component style={style} />

// ❌ BAD - Creates new array on every render
<List items={[1, 2, 3]} />

// ✅ GOOD - Define outside
const items = [1, 2, 3];
<List items={items} />
```

## Accessibility

### Always Include

```tsx
// Labels for inputs
<label htmlFor="email">Email</label>
<input id="email" type="email" />

// Alt text for images
<Image src="/logo.png" alt="Company Logo" />

// ARIA labels for icon buttons
<button aria-label="Close modal">
  <CloseIcon />
</button>

// Keyboard navigation
<div 
  role="button" 
  tabIndex={0}
  onKeyDown={(e) => e.key === 'Enter' && handleClick()}
  onClick={handleClick}
>
  Click Me
</div>
```

## Comments

### When to Comment

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Explain WHY, not WHAT
// Use floor division to avoid floating point errors in token calculations
const tokenAmount = Math.floor(value * 10 ** decimals);

// ✅ GOOD - Document complex business logic
/**
 * Calculates the health factor of a borrow position
 * Health factor < 1.0 means position is at risk of liquidation
 * Formula: (collateralValue * liquidationThreshold) / borrowValue
 */
const calculateHealthFactor = (collateral: number, borrow: number) => {
  return (collateral * 0.8) / borrow;
};

// ❌ BAD - Stating the obvious
// Set the user name to 'John'
const userName = 'John';

// ❌ BAD - Commented out code (delete it instead)
// const oldFunction = () => {
//   // old implementation
// };
```

### JSDoc for Functions

```typescript
/**
 * Validates a wallet address
 * @param address - The wallet address to validate
 * @returns True if valid Ethereum address
 */
export const isValidAddress = (address: string): boolean => {
  return /^0x[a-fA-F0-9]{40}$/.test(address);
};

